{{External|rs=Evil Twin}}
[[File:Molly (3) chathead.png|left|One of Molly's Appearances.]]
'''Evil twin''' is a [[Random events|random event]] in which the player is [[Teleportation|teleported]] into a room at an unknown location by [[Postie Pete]], at the request of [[Molly]]. She claims her twin sister has been committing crimes around ''RuneScape'', and she was being blamed for it. Although she has finally been able to capture her sister, she has also dragged several other female bystanders with her, and now she needs the player to help her separate her from the innocent bystanders.
[[File:Evil twin control panel.png|thumb|300px|The [[Control panel (Evil twin)|control panel]].]]
Her sister and the other women are in a large pen in the room next to the one Molly is in. Once players leave the first room, they can't see anything until their task is complete. However, clicking on the door will make Molly's [[chathead]] appear, giving players a hint if they forgot what she looked like.

The goal of this random event is for players to go the other room and use the [[control panel (Evil twin)|controllers]] of a [[evil claw|crane]] to choose the evil twin between the suspects. Players get a maximum of two chances to choose the correct person. Once the evil twin has been successfully captured, Molly will reward the player with 2-5 uncut [[gems]], up to diamond.

If players fail to choose the evil twin, they will be teleported to a random location in Gielinor with no reward. For both members and free-to-play players, there are 34 distinct locations that Molly may choose to teleport the player, most of them in fairly obscure locations not commonly visited by players.

